Would it be possible to add an easier way of handling optional properties in `JsonDocument`(s)?

Many APIs that return JSON include optional values depending upon the options they are called with. Currently it is very cumbersome to handling this with `System.Text.Json`.

Consider the following JSON structure:

```json
[
    {
         "id": 1,
        "name": "Example 1",
        "links": {
            "self": "https://example.com/models/1"
        }
    },
    {
        "id": 2,
        "name": "Example 2",
        "optionalId": 12345
    }
]
```

Handling this structure with `Newtonsoft.Json` is fairly straightforward:

```csharp
ar json = JArray.Parse(await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync());

return json.Select(value => new MyDomainObject {
    Id = ...,
    Name = ...,
    OptionalId = (int?)value["optionalId"]
}).ToList();
```

With `System.Text.Json` this is pretty awkward:

```csharp
using var document = JsonDocument.Parse(await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync());

var values = new List<MyDomainObject>();

foreach (var value in document.RootElement.EnumerateArray())
{
    JsonElement optionalId;
    bool hasOptionalId = false;
    int optionalId = 0;
    if (value.TryGetProperty("optionalId", out optionalId))
    {
         hasOptionalId = optionalId .TryGetInt32(out optionalIdValue);
    }

    values.Add(new MyDomainObject {
        Id = ...,
        Name = ...,
        OptionalId = hasOptionalId ? optionalIdValue : default(int?)
    });
}
```

And if you need to do this for multiple properties it gets ugly IMO.

Further if you want to get the nested object `links` that could potentially exist it's really weird to retrieve that.

Currently I've been doing this:

```csharp
string uri = null;

try
{
    uri = json.GetProperty("links").GetProperty("self").GetString();
}
catch (KeyNotFoundException)
{
}
```

What I would like to see is something like this:

```csharp
var optionalId = value.GetProperty("optional")?.GetInt32();

var uri = value.GetProperty("links")?.GetProperty("self")?.GetString();
```

or something that achieves the same.

